PRD: Smart IoT Waste Sorting Bin
Product overview

A smart waste bin that detects a person approaching with an ultrasonic sensor, captures waste using an ESP32-CAM, sends the image/video to a backend AI model for detection and classification, and displays the result on a frontend dashboard. The system classifies waste into three categories: plastic, metal, and organic.

1) Firmware PRD
Product name

ESP32-CAM Waste Detection Firmware

Purpose

Control the bin hardware, detect user presence, capture waste imagery, send data to the backend, and trigger the sorting mechanism based on the backend response.

Goals
Detect human presence using the ultrasonic sensor.
Open the bin lid when presence is confirmed.
Capture image or short video of the waste.
Send captured media to the backend reliably.
Receive classification response from backend.
Control three servos to sort waste into the correct category.
Reset the bin to idle after each cycle.
Users
End users disposing waste.
System operator or maintainer.
