Database management
Cloud deployment orchestration
Functional requirements
The firmware shall monitor the ultrasonic sensor continuously.
When a person is detected within a configured threshold, the firmware shall enter an active sorting state.
The firmware shall open the lid using Servo 1.
The firmware shall capture waste imagery using ESP32-CAM.
The firmware shall send the captured image or stream snapshot to the backend through HTTP or MQTT.
The firmware shall wait for a classification result from the backend.
The firmware shall move Servo 2 to the appropriate tray position based on the classification.
The firmware shall activate Servo 3 to release waste into the selected compartment.
The firmware shall return all servos to the default position after sorting.
The firmware shall log basic status events for debugging.
Non-functional requirements
Low latency response after presence detection.
Stable Wi-Fi reconnection after signal loss.
Reliable servo timing and movement.
Minimal false triggering from ultrasonic noise.
Power-efficient idle mode.
