Error handling
If Wi-Fi fails, retry connection.
If backend times out, retry capture or mark as unresolved.
If servo movement fails, stop the cycle and raise an error state.
If ultrasonic gives unstable readings, require repeated detection before activation.
Acceptance criteria
The bin detects presence correctly within the configured distance range.
The lid opens and closes without manual intervention.
Captured images are sent successfully to the backend.
The correct servo sequence runs after backend classification.
The bin returns to idle after sorting.
The firmware recovers from temporary Wi-Fi failures.


